No ownership or rights are claimed over these technologies or data sources.

This project uses publicly available data and open-source technologies, including:
NASA POWER API – historical weather and climate data
Natural Earth – open-source geographic datasets
Docker – containerization platform
StarRocks – open-source analytical database
Apache Kafka – distributed streaming platform

Project Description

This project is created mainly for educational purposes. Its goal is to build a console application that allows downloading historical weather data from the NASA POWER API and streaming this data into StarRocks via Apache Kafka and Kafka Connect. The project compares different query approaches and their performance in StarRocks.
